[h1]$_SERVER[/h1]

$_SERVER['HTTP_HOST'] returns the Host header from the current request. [code format="php"]<?php
echo $_SERVER['HTTP_HOST'];
//Outputs "localhost"
?>[/code]
This method can be useful when you have a lot of images on your server and need to transfer the website to another host. Instead of changing the path for each image, you can do the following:
Create a [b]config.php[/b] file, that holds the path to your images: [code format="php" ]<?php
$host = $_SERVER['HTTP_HOST'];
$image_path = $host.'/images/';
?>[/code]
Use the [b]config.php[/b] file in your scripts:[code format="php" ]<?php
require 'config.php';
echo '<img src="'.$image_path.'header.png" />';
?>[/code]
[note]The path to your images is now dynamic. It will change automatically, based on the Host header.[/note]
